                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; reddish-brown; red.</seg>
                        <persName ref="PRS10788WaldaMuse" role="scribe">Walda Muse</persName>The handwriting is identical to that of Walda Muse (cp. also the ruling pattern and the ornamental bands). See Mss. MR-004, MR-009, MR-014b, MR-023, MR-016, AGM-009.<date>Second half of the 19th cent.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ቅ for ቅዱስ</item>
                           <item>ሰአ for ሰአል</item>
                           <item>ሰ for ሰላም</item>
                           <item>ይዲ for ይቤ፡ ዲያቆን</item>
                           <item>ይሕ for ይቤ፡ ሕዝብ</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the Trinitarian formula in the incipit page of the text (fol. 3r); incipit of the subsections; elements of the punctuation signs, elements of Ethiopic numerals;</seg>
